<CascadingAuthenticationState>
    <Router AppAssembly="typeof(Program).Assembly">
        <Found Context="routeData">
            @* The render-mode cascade is intentionally PER-PAGE in this
               app. There is no layout-level or router-level cascade
               because every legal placement has the same shape of bug:

               (a) `@rendermode` on `<AuthorizeRouteView>` — its
                   templated `<NotAuthorized>` child is a
                   `RenderFragment<T>` that can't be serialized across
                   a render-mode boundary. Verbatim exception:

                       System.InvalidOperationException:
                           Cannot pass RenderFragment<T> parameter
                           'NotAuthorized' to component
                           'AuthorizeRouteView' with rendermode
                           'InteractiveServerRenderMode'.
                           Templated content can't be passed across a
                           rendermode boundary, because it is arbitrary
                           code and cannot be serialized.

               (b) `@rendermode` on the LAYOUT (any
                   `LayoutComponentBase` such as MainLayout,
                   AccountLayout) — the framework tries to serialize
                   the layout's `@Body` parameter for streaming SSR and
                   a `Body`-shaped `RenderFragment` is also arbitrary
                   code. Verbatim exception (the symptom that shipped
                   in round-AC-2):

                       System.InvalidOperationException:
                           Cannot pass the parameter 'Body' to
                           component 'MainLayout' with rendermode
                           'InteractiveServerRenderMode'. This is
                           because the parameter is of the delegate
                           type 'RenderFragment', which is arbitrary
                           code and cannot be serialized.

               So every interactive page MUST carry its own
               `@rendermode InteractiveServer` directive at the top of
               the .razor file (after `@page`/`@attribute`/`@layout`).
               Pages without the directive render as static SSR once
               and never wire up an interactive SignalR circuit — fine
               for `Weather.razor` (with `[StreamRendering]` for
               streaming server output) and `Error.razor`, but wrong
               for any page that takes user input or fires
               `OnInitializedAsync` callbacks against ApplicationDbContext.

               Per-page opt-out: in .NET 9 the `@rendermode` directive
               only accepts `InteractiveServer` /
               `InteractiveWebAssembly` / `InteractiveAuto`; there is
               no "Static" value, and static rendering is the implicit
               default when no interactive ancestor provides the
               mode. So a page that wants true static SSR simply omits
               the directive.

               Account pages (Login, Register, ForgotPassword,
               ResetPassword, Manage, ChangePassword) flow through
               this AuthorizeRouteView: they're matched by the
               Router's Found template, AuthorizeRouteView's
               Authorized default branch passes through (no
               `[Authorize]` attribute on some of them), and they're
               wrapped by AccountLayout. Each of them now carries an
               explicit `@rendermode InteractiveServer` directive so
               they wire up interactive SignalR even without a layout
               cascade. Form submissions now happen via Blazor
               enhanced navigation rather than a hard form POST; the
               `?ReturnUrl=` round-trip's `forceLoad: true` (Login /
               Register) still hard-reloads so the auth cookie is
               honored by the next page render. *@
            <AuthorizeRouteView RouteData="routeData"
                                DefaultLayout="typeof(Layout.MainLayout)">
                <NotAuthorized>
                    <RedirectToLogin />
                </NotAuthorized>
            </AuthorizeRouteView>
            <FocusOnNavigate RouteData="routeData" Selector="h1" />
        </Found>
    </Router>
</CascadingAuthenticationState>
